; A. Description
;    A list of commands here configures CRC module and generates a crc16 result computed from specific data.
;
; B. Preparation
;    N/A
;
; C. Prerequisite Example (abov_example_config.h)
;    1. CRC 
;
; D. Note
;    Should use Online CRC calculation to compare the result.
;    Link : http://www.ghsi.de/pages/subpages/Online%20CRC%20Calculation/
;
; Please, read the User Manual of the specific chip for more details.
;
; CRC0
; 1. Channel                   : 0 (CRC0)
;
; 2. Config                    : [ 0 p c t m ]
;    Operation                 : p (Polling)
;    Mode                      : c (CRC)
;    CRC Poly                  : t (CRC-16)
;    First-In Bit              : m (MSB)
;
; 3. Data                      : [ 0 7 0x30 0x31 0x32 0x33 0x34 0x35 0x36 ]
;    Data Length               : 7
;    Data                      : 0x30 ... (Hexa and space (delimitor))
;
; CRC-16 Poly       : x^16 + x^15 + x^2 + x^0
; Result of CRC-16  : 0x826e

; CRC0
sendln 'cm crc'
mpause 30
sendln 'uninit 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'init 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'config 0 p c t m'
mpause 30
sendln 'data 0 7 0x30 0x31 0x32 0x33 0x34 0x35 0x36'
mpause 30
sendln 'cmpt 0 7'
